Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.73,0:00:03.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.51,0:00:05.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.31,0:00:06.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.33,0:00:08.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Danger is approaching, Haibara, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:10.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even the cast is getting insanely large!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.15,0:00:12.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.75,0:00:14.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a child\Nbut has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.52,0:00:16.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.05,0:01:42.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On the way home from school,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:47.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara and I saw a car belonging to Gin, one of the men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.71,0:01:50.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I set up a bug in his car, and we followed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:57.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But Gin found the bug, and figured out that Haibara was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.98,0:02:01.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}By intercepting his conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.45,0:02:03.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}we found out about their murder plans,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:07.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so we went to a party at Haido City Hotel being held in memory of a film director.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.10,0:02:15.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. That lawyer's gone already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.59,0:02:16.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.47,0:02:17.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.54,0:02:48.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:50.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:51.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:55.92,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.17,0:02:57.63,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.17,0:02:59.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something happened, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:00.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.94,0:03:02.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:05.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Would someone mind giving me an explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.09,0:03:08.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, calm down.\NI'm Megure, from the Metro Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:14.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's new. For once you police arrived quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.61,0:03:18.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We got a tip that there was going to be a murder tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:22.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that someone was planning to kill this Nomiguchi person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:30.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.80,0:03:32.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:33.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.95,0:03:35.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.19,0:03:37.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell police headquarters right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.33,0:03:37.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.06,0:03:41.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:46.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A partner of the men in black who shrunk me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:49.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Codename Pisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.99,0:03:51.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's still somewhere in this hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.74,0:03:54.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.32,0:04:02.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were the ones closest to\NMr. Nomiguchi when the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.37,0:04:03.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:06.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see anyone suspicious at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:09.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:12.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was almost turned into a pencil board too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:16.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. The{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier scratched my suit like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:20.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never saw any suspicious characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:21.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:25.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, she says she didn't see anyone of the sort, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was an accident, an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.19,0:04:31.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier's chains were old, and broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.86,0:04:35.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lawyer just happened to be under it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:38.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a message saying there'd be a murder tonight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.71,0:04:40.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:46.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you go investigating us, I'd like a full description of the informer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.27,0:04:50.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the informer is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:55.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The voice was altered by a machine, so we don't even know if it was a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.24,0:04:58.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was probably a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.55,0:05:03.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Nomiguchi was weakened by his medical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.21,0:05:04.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The accident just happened to overlap with the prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.90,0:05:10.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The heavens smote him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.65,0:05:12.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do bad things, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:18.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you eat at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.20,0:05:22.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An insignificant lad like yourself should keep his mouth shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.19,0:05:31.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Someone call the chef!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.90,0:05:34.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Was there a cockroach in it or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.55,0:05:37.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're eating at a time like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.84,0:05:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the heavens smote you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.90,0:05:41.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.00,0:05:41.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, keep it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.81,0:05:44.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is... a piece of the{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10} chan{\r\be10}delier's chain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:46.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why was it in a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.65,0:05:48.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:54.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Nomiguchi died when he was crushed by the falling{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.26,0:05:59.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To murder someone that way, you'd have to set a trap on the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:04.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,lure him underneath it when the lights were turned off,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.06,0:06:06.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then activate the trap, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.78,0:06:12.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, looking at the fallen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier and the ceiling it hung from,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:15.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, murder is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.68,0:06:21.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you understand, could you release us already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.94,0:06:28.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:32.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Dropping a{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10} chan{\r\be10}delier on a targeted individual in the darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:34.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}without some sort of trap, would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:38.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yet, he did just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.56,0:06:41.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:47.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.20,0:06:53.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Staying here and wasting time is too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And how will you explain us being here if Inspector Megure or the others spot us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:03.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You only have one clue—the piece of chain you picked up earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.31,0:07:08.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even you could figure out who the killer is from just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.58,0:07:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if I have two?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.29,0:07:15.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It fell after the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}delier, but before the lights were turned back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:18.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like it has the killer's name written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:26.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at its corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.90,0:07:30.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It says "Director Sakamaki's Mourning Party", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.91,0:07:34.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Its owner probably received it at the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:37.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look around at the guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.09,0:07:40.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, that man holding the glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.87,0:07:42.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the overweight woman next to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.87,0:07:45.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the elderly man with the mustache in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.29,0:07:49.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They all have this handkerchief, but in different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.55,0:07:50.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:56.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Likely, due to Director Sakamaki's number one hit, "The Rainbow Handkerchief",
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:07:59.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,handkerchiefs in seven different colors were given to the guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:02.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if we ask at the front desk,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.18,0:08:06.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we can reduce the number of suspects to those that received a purple handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.78,0:08:11.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But is there really any connection between that and the murder?{でも、それが本当にあの殺人に関係している物がどうかなんて...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:14.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I don't yet know how it was used,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or even if it belonged to the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.65,0:08:21.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a non-zero probability of it being related to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.74,0:08:22.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.69,0:08:28.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can go to the bathroom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:31.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.10,0:08:36.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you all?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.76,0:08:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Mr. Nomiguchi really pass away?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.25,0:08:40.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.95,0:08:42.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.45,0:08:46.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll explain it later, so please everyone, back away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:49.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Please answer us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The people we gave purple handkerchiefs to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.21,0:09:17.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I picked one up,\Nso I want to return it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:21.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were going to use the handkerchiefs later for something, weren't they?{あのハンカチ、後で何かに使うつもりだったんでしょ？HANKACHI clearly in the plural here according to the manga.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:23.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. At the end of the party, we were going to choose a color,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.91,0:09:29.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and someone with that color handkerchief would be chosen to say a few words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:33.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me their names. I'll look for someone who doesn't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:38.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.64,0:09:41.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep holding them in, it'll turn into a panic!{これ以上　引き留めたらパニックになりかねん！}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.38,0:09:44.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However you look at it, it doesn't look like anything but an accident.{どうみても事故にしか見えんし}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:46.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's get out of here.{[ここは]ひとまず帰すか...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.61,0:09:47.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:49.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The guests who were given purple handkerchiefs are these seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.60,0:09:55.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.25,0:09:56.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.20,0:09:59.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I see. So it was one of those seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.27,0:10:05.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm not certain, but it's likely that among those seven
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.02,0:10:06.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}is one of them, Pisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:08.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, they're coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:12.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, when the accident happened,{[すいません！]事故があった時}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.68,0:10:13.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,were you nearby?{側にいましたか！？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:15.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know! Now outta my way!{知らん！そこをどいてくれ！！}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.49,0:10:17.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us the details of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.78,0:10:19.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to the police about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:23.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. Let's go back to the doc's car for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:24.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:28.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:30.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.75,0:10:32.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wai—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.96,0:10:34.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.66,0:10:36.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)}Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.68,0:10:48.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.57,0:10:50.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up! Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:53.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.93,0:10:55.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:10:58.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:00.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in class right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:08.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be because of your cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.55,0:11:11.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You really should go rest in the nurse's office...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.72,0:11:12.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.44,0:11:16.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it... That's it, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.05,0:11:20.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Randomly meeting them in town is just too good to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:23.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've been having dreams like this a lot lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.04,0:11:27.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Maybe I'm just exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.21,0:11:29.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.26,0:11:31.30,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Answer me, Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.92,0:11:32.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.91,0:11:33.81,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.35,0:11:35.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:36.13,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:37.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.79,0:11:38.66,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:44.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:46.60,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara? Is that you, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.21,0:11:48.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:50.26,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm in the doc's car in front of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.11,0:11:54.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm speaking to you through the microphone and speaker in the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.92,0:11:56.61,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:11:58.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I want to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:01.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in the hallway, in front of the party room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:03.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of the party room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.75,0:12:09.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, back then I got engulfed by a wave of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.95,0:12:11.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and got separated from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.30,0:12:14.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then someone came from behind me and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.98,0:12:19.15,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Someone came from behind you and...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.18,0:12:22.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody made me sniff some drug,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:25.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and now I'm being confined in some winecellar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.87,0:12:27.65,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey... By "somebody", you mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:29.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:35.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Likely the Organization member who managed to commit murder in front of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:37.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:39.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.06,0:12:42.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not there, is he? I mean, right next to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:43.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.77,0:12:46.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever he is, he's not here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:50.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the door is locked tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.47,0:12:54.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing around is a large cardboard box and cart for carrying goods
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.85,0:12:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and an employee boiler suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:57.91,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Boiler suit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.44,0:12:59.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.33,0:13:03.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Likely, after making me sniff the drug, he must have taken me to the restroom or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.34,0:13:08.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,changed into this previously prepared boiler suit, then stuffed me in the box and brought me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.53,0:13:13.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably ready in case the attempt on that lawyer's life failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.43,0:13:17.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd have lured the lawyer to the restroom and killed him, then brought him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.75,0:13:23.18,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Whatever. Just hurry and find a way out of there, and find our next move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.47,0:13:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? Listen well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Apoptoxin 4869 that regressed us to childhood, the "apo" stands for "apoptosis".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.32,0:13:36.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, programmed cell destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.60,0:13:38.30,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.70,0:13:41.14,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Cells have a mechanism that forces them to self-destruct,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.14,0:13:44.65,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and we live because they receive a signal limiting that process.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.34,0:13:46.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.44,0:13:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this drug doesn't just activate apoptosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:56.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It also contains a telomerase, and increases a cell's reproductive ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.95,0:14:01.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Haibara! I'll listen to as much as you want about that once you get out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:04.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.96,0:14:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never... never be able to exchange words with you ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.48,0:14:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.43,0:14:12.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:18.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They held me here despite being in my shrunken figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.55,0:14:25.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I were to escape from here, they'd find me in no more than two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:32.01,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that happens, the doctor who protected me, and all others who were involved with me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:35.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}would be killed to preserve their secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.60,0:14:37.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.12,0:14:41.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter if I die here or if I escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:47.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already been forced into a state where I can no longer come into contact with any of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:49.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:55.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I'm going to tell you all I can remember about the drug, as long as I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.57,0:15:00.40,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Tada! Dr. Agasa's Great Adventure II!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.89,0:15:03.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... what was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.05,0:15:08.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's the doctor's game that Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} returned to me at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were probably checking the MO disc in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.52,0:15:17.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cell phone attached to the PC, which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.70,0:15:20.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were analyzing my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.86,0:15:26.28,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, you aren't tied up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:28.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm in such a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.57,0:15:33.31,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They won't leave me for long without tying me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:37.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he won't be able to come back for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.18,0:15:41.43,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After you disappeared, I called the inspector right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.40,0:15:48.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and told him to not let the guests with purple handkerchiefs leave the Haido City Hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.68,0:15:50.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with Shin'ichi Kudo's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:56.05,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That you aren't tied up, and that they left a PC connected to a cell phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.98,0:15:59.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,likely means that the person who confined you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:02.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,tried to leave the hotel for a bit in order to complete some sort of objective,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:06.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when they were stopped by the officers at the exit, and made to undergo police questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.58,0:16:08.55,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Also, there's a good{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10} chan{\r\be10}ce
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:11.36,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}that they're in a state where they can't communicate with the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.12,0:16:15.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already been almost an hour since you vanished,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.88,0:16:20.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it would be unthinkable for neither him or his colleagues to not have come there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's there. One of the seven I chose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.65,0:16:28.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the one who did the assassination and confined you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:31.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is the one called Pisco!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this place is still somewhere in the Haido City Hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.15,0:16:37.47,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.47,0:16:43.35,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I can prove the murder before he contacts his companions, and reveal him to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:46.20,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}then your secret will remain intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At best, the inspector can hold those seven for another hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.48,0:16:55.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going to the hotel's front desk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.10,0:16:57.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to ask them if there's any infrequently used winecellar in the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.80,0:16:59.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll go and save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.73,0:17:02.05,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I say there's a girl locked in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:03.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.64,0:17:07.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you what'd happen to those involved with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.32,0:17:13.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't complain to me, whatever happens to the staff members who help me escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.37,0:17:17.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then find some way to get out of there by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:21.86,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In the meantime, I'll find Pisco out from those seven people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.36,0:17:25.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's really easy to say and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:28.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no escape route in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.18,0:17:31.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing here is an old chimney.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.21,0:17:33.21,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Can you climb up that chimney?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:39.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's too big to climb up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:44.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I weren't in this body, it looks like I could barely manage it by stretching my arms and legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.11,0:17:45.16,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Isn't there some sort of rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:49.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not sure. Do they keep ropes in a winecellar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.23,0:17:53.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's a winecellar, does it mean it has a wide variety of alcoholic drinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.31,0:17:56.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they took an old room that had fallen into disuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:18:00.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and turned it into a winecellar where they stored alcoholic beverages from around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.32,0:18:02.65,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is there baigar there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.23,0:18:04.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Baigar?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.08,0:18:06.36,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah. It's a strong liquor from China.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:08.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.40,0:18:09.51,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just look around for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see if there's some.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:14.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what do you want that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:15.95,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How's your cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.75,0:18:18.56,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You said you had a cold in the morning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.29,0:18:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your topic seems to jump all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.09,0:18:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Just tell me how you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:28.75,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After my sleeping on the floor, I think my fever went up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:29.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.71,0:18:30.48,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.48,0:18:32.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sound quite happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.92,0:18:33.92,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:37.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found the baigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:41.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what am I supposed to do with this liquor?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.35,0:18:43.81,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm going to get you out of that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.73,0:18:47.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By casting the ultimate magic spell on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.66,0:18:53.42,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\an8}This was the scene inside the hotel, right after the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.42,0:18:59.74,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\an8}Even now, many people are still being questioned in a nearby room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:02.55,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}However, those individuals' names have yet to be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.44,0:19:05.35,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That is all. This is being broadcast live from the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.26,0:19:10.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From that news report, I figured out the rough location of the seven right after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.83,0:19:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.31,0:19:16.73,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, do you know how to spell "Hercule Poirot"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.08,0:19:20.95,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What the heck are you doing? Did you drink the baigar already?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.44,0:19:23.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I drank it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:28.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're planning, but I feel even worse now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:31.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, tell me how to spell Poirot's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.29,0:19:37.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"H-E-R-C-U-L-E P-O-I-R-O-T", but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:38.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,380)}What do you want to know that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.38,0:19:44.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to transfer the drug's data from the Organization's computer to the doctor's MO disc,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:47.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I got stuck on the password.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.39,0:19:48.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...R-O-T.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.34,0:19:52.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good. It's not Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:55.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you think the password might be "Poirot"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.00,0:20:01.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The people in the Organization called the drug by a name during its prototype phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.87,0:20:06.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They gave it the serial number 4869/{\i1}shiyaroku{\i0} after Sherlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.39,0:20:09.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They called it the "Incomplete Detective".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.85,0:20:13.56,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So I've been trying the names of great detectives as they popped into my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.89,0:20:17.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess it's not going to be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:18.10,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Shelling Ford".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:24.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(170,0)}The spelling is "S-H-E-L-L-I-N-G F-O-R-D".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:26.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there such a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.67,0:20:27.63,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just try it and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.93,0:20:32.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-H-E-L-L-I-N-G F-O-R-D.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.93,0:20:38.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It opened! How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.16,0:20:40.81,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Shelling Ford" was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:47.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...a temporary name that Conan Doyle gave to his detective before naming him Sherlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:51.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's the prototype of the Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:54.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's kind of clever for the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:20:56.85,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Anyway, we're running out of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:20:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't your body feel odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.75,0:21:03.11,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How could it not, after you had me down liquor like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.92,0:21:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I'll drop the drug's data on this MO disc and hide it in this winecellar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.95,0:21:15.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll come get it later, right? After the Organization takes me away...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:16.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:19.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Shin'ichi! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.05,0:21:28.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's them. Could Pisco have gotten through to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.07,0:21:34.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that can't be! The Inspector said he'd call me before releasing those seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.49,0:21:36.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could there be a tracking device in the PC Haibara's using?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.92,0:21:45.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. They called him and there was no answer, so they used the tracking device to get here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.60,0:21:47.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara, this is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.94,0:21:50.88,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They're coming! For now, go hide in the chimney or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.90,0:21:54.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.97,0:21:55.49,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.50,0:21:59.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! It's Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Men dressed in black?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.59,0:24:09.57,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.50,0:24:26.18,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.38,0:23:48.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pisco's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.24,0:23:50.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A burn mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.25,0:23:52.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That means this chain...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.41,0:23:57.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I see. That's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.55,0:24:04.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I missed you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.63,0:24:05.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sherry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.22,0:24:09.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.25,0:24:14.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan: "Reunion with the Black Organization (Case Closed)"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.53,0:24:20.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Fluorescent Paint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.50,0:24:21.88,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, an amazing development!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.88,0:24:24.84,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're not feeling well, it's not good to drink too much.
